500 g Ground Beef and Pork Mix
¾ cup Basmati Rice
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
1 unit(s) Green Onion
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Ketchup
2 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 tbsp Vegetable Stock Powder
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Once water is boiling, add rice, stock powder and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Stir to combine.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Finely chop green onion.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions and peppers.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender-crisp, 3-4 min.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer veggies to a plate and cover to keep warm.

Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef and pork mix.
Cook, breaking up meat into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Season with salt and pepper.

Reduce heat to medium.
Add Mexican Seasoning, garlic, ketchup and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water to the pan with beef and pork. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min.
When rice is done, add veggies and rice to the pan. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Reduce heat to low, then sprinkle cheese over top. Cover and cook until cheese melts, 2-3 min.

Divide beef and pork skillet rice between plates.
Sprinkle green onions over top.

If you've opted for double beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the regular portion of beef. Work in batches, if necessary.